Defendant Frenchie Charles Holloway Jr appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Robert Lee Taylor in court for Frenchie Charles Holloway Jr.  Prosecuting Attorney Gregg Herman in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Court took judicial notice of the defendants prior convictions. Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer Brian Czapla.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 41 and remains calendared for 10/11 at 8:30am.

If an Electronic Monitoring Device (GPS) is unavailable and Cash Bail has been paid, Defendant to be released and placed on the Electronic Monitoring (GPS) waiting list. Defendant Frenchie Charles Holloway in court with attorney Michael V Fuentes.  Defendant Frenchie Charles Holloway in custody at MSDF.  Sara Beth Hill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Frenchie Charles Holloway appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Rosa, Branch 35.
